line_1: And act the tyrant with good-nature.
line_2: Mould into smiles each pretty feature,

line_1: And all be burst with pure Good-nature.
line_2: Else We should want both Gibe and Satyr;

line_1: Only one has more grace, and the other good-nature.
line_2: They're alike in age, family, fortune, and feature,

line_1: And slander itself must allow him good-nature:
line_2: Here Hickey reclines, a most blunt, pleasant creature,

line_1: And tipped her arrows with good-nature.
line_2: Had armed with spirit, wit, and satire:
